usecase.friends.relationship

Class BiDiRelationNetwork

  • java.lang.Object
    • usecase.friends.relationship.BiDiRelationNetwork
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, RelationNetwork

    public class BiDiRelationNetwork
extends java.lang.Object
implements RelationNetwork
    A Bi-Direction Graph implementation of Relationship Manage. Which means, a relation is always duel sided: p1 is connected to p2 implies p2 is connected to p1.

        public void applyConnectionOffset(java.util.UUID p1,
                                  java.util.UUID p2,
                                  int offset)
        Description copied from interface: RelationNetwork
        Apply a offset in the layers of connection, without violating the class invariant. i.e. if the offset would make the layers of connection becomes negative or over Integer.MAX_VALUE, it will be adjusted to the nearest bound.
